Issues Found in app.tsx
1. Fixed Positioning with inset-0
TSX
<div className="fixed inset-0 bg-[#0f172a] ...">
The root container uses fixed positioning with inset-0. This can cause issues in embedded environments like Google AI Studio because:

Fixed positioning is relative to the viewport, not the parent container
Embedded iframes or preview panels may not handle fixed elements correctly
2. Overflow Hidden Everywhere
TSX
className="... overflow-hidden"
Multiple overflow-hidden declarations can clip content unexpectedly in certain viewport configurations.

3. Complex Nested Flex with min-h-0
The combination of flex-1 min-h-0 in nested containers can cause height calculation issues in some rendering environments.

Recommended Fixes
Here's a modified version of your root container:

TSX
// Option 1: Use min-h-screen instead of fixed positioning
return (
    <div className="min-h-screen h-screen bg-[#0f172a] text-white flex flex-col overflow-x-hidden font-sans select-none">
        {/* ... rest of your code */}
    </div>
);
TSX
// Option 2: Use absolute positioning with a relative parent
return (
    <div className="relative w-full h-screen">
        <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-[#0f172a] text-white flex flex-col overflow-hidden font-sans select-none">
            {/* ... rest of your code */}
        </div>
    </div>
);
TSX
// Option 3: Simplest - just use viewport units directly
return (
    <div className="w-screen h-screen bg-[#0f172a] text-white flex flex-col overflow-hidden font-sans select-none">
        {/* ... rest of your code */}
    </div>
);
Additional Recommendations
Issue	Current	Fix
Root positioning	fixed inset-0	min-h-screen or h-screen
Main overflow	overflow-hidden	overflow-auto or overflow-y-auto
Nested flex containers	Multiple min-h-0	Use flex-shrink-0 where needed

